On Wed, Jul 17, 2013 at 12:43 AM, Bernd Fischer <bernd.fischer at embl.de> wrote:
> Hi, I used the new BiocStyles package in the experimental data package HD2013SGI and
> checked the code in to the trunc. I expected to see changes only in the devel version, but
> not in the release version.
> The BUILD/CHECK reports now show an error in the release
> version (because BiocStyles is obviously not available).
>
> Is there anything going wrong with the separation of devel and release for experimental data packages?
>


No; there is no branching for experiment data packages, so the same
exact package is built on both the release and devel machines.

You don't need to do anything, as the last successfully built version
of the package has already propagated to our release repository.

Dan


